cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.MM

The paper deals with joint sparsity in compressed sensing, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The use of iterative support detection (ISD) and convex relaxation algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The mention of feature learning and multi-channel sparse Bernoulli signal also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SI (Signal Processing). Finally, the use of numerical experiments suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
